SELECT CASE WHEN MAX("log_logged_timestamp") IS NULL THEN 1000000 
            ELSE MAX("log_logged_timestamp") + 1
       END AS "log_logged_timestamp"
FROM "ods_lineage_log"

7430.text:
Extract all the SQL executed above the high water mark, into a new table **tmp_lineage_log**

To make this component validate and run, supply valid values for all the private job variables.

7431.text: Run the transformation job to transform and copy the data from bronze to its permanent home in the silver layer

7432.text:
Create the SQL log table **ods_lineage_log**.
In a medallion data architecture this is a silver layer object, so only create the table if it does not already exist.

7433.text:
Fetch the latest timestamp loaded (the high water mark) into a job variable.
Default to a long time in the past if no data has ever been loaded.

1.value:
SELECT INDEX as "sql_index",
       ("i"."Data Value":"loggedTimestamp")::VARCHAR AS "loggedTimestamp",
       ("i"."Data Value":"componentCanvasName")::VARCHAR AS "componentCanvasName",
       ("i"."Data Value":"componentName")::VARCHAR AS "componentName",
       ("i"."Data Value":"endTimestamp")::NUMBER AS "endTimestamp",
       ("i"."Data Value":"environment":"name")::VARCHAR AS "env_name",
       ("i"."Data Value":"environment":"database")::VARCHAR AS "database",
       ("i"."Data Value":"environment":"schema")::VARCHAR AS "schema",
       ("i"."Data Value":"environment":"url")::VARCHAR AS "url",
       ("i"."Data Value":"environment":"user")::VARCHAR AS "user",
       ("i"."Data Value":"job":"name")::VARCHAR AS "job_name",
       ("i"."Data Value":"job":"type")::VARCHAR AS "job_type",
       ("i"."Data Value":"sourceUsername")::VARCHAR AS "sourceUsername",
       ("f1".Value:"dialect")::VARCHAR AS "dialect",
       ("f1".Value:"query")::VARCHAR AS "query",
       ("i"."Data Value":"startTimestamp")::NUMBER AS "startTimestamp",
       ("i"."Data Value":"urlPath")::VARCHAR AS "urlPath",
       ("i"."Data Value":"sourceConnectionUrl")::VARCHAR AS "sourceConnectionUrl",
       ("i"."Data Value":"taskType")::VARCHAR AS "taskType"
FROM $T{tmp_lineage_log} "i",
     LATERAL FLATTEN (input => "i"."Data Value":"sql") "f1"

7447.text:
Change the granularity of the data to 1 row per SQL statement executed - and extract fields to columns

Also store the INDEX field from the flatten - to preserve the order of the SQL statements in the array (when a single component executes multiple SQL statements, such as an ingestion component)

7448.text:
In a medallion data architecture this is a bronze-to-silver layer data transformation.
It appends data to the silver layer target table **ods_lineage_log** from the bronze layer source table **tmp_lineage_log**.
